  "prompt": "Are images shared through wechat encrypted? Are they stored in servers? What is the chance of them getting leaked?",
  "response": "WeChat uses encryption for messages and media, but no system is 100% secure. Here's a balanced overview:\n\nEncryption:\n- Messages and images are encrypted during transmission\n- End-to-end encryption for personal chats\n- Less secure for group chats and official accounts\n\nServer Storage:\n- Images are temporarily stored on WeChat servers\n- Servers located primarily in China\n- Subject to Chinese data protection/access laws\n\nPotential Leak Risks:\n- Low direct technical risk of random hacking\n- Higher potential risk from:\n  1. Government access\n  2. Internal employee access\n  3. Potential data breaches\n  4. Compromised accounts\n\nRecommendations:\n- Use strong account password\n- Enable two-factor authentication\n- Be cautious about sensitive images\n- Assume nothing is 100% private\n\nFor maximum privacy, consider:\n- Avoiding highly sensitive images\n- Using additional encryption\n- Being aware of potential surveillance\n\nThe exact leak probability can't be precisely quantified, but general digital security best practices are recommended.",
